narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: French 140 is a great grammar review as well as a great way to learn how to speak better.
I would recommend it for another student if French is their chosen second language.

French 140 was a good class. Before I took the class, I had hoped to improve my writing and speech, and I feel that I indeed have improved in these areas after taking this course. Professor Wing is encouraging, funny, and cool overall. I would recommend taking this class.
You work on your french every day, read plenty of novels. Plenty of work, but you also learn plenty of french.
French 140 is a solid continuation of French 130--more challenging texts, more vocabulary, more complex grammar. The workload is not substantially heavier. I would recommend it.

4. Its an L4 French class. Take it if you need to. I was bored to tears at first, since I thought I could just jump straight to L5, but the intensive correction on speaking and writing was very helpful.
